      <section eId="sec_44_12_171">
        <num>44-12-171</num>
        <content>
          <p>When the plaintiff in a trover action has replevied the property and on the trial of the case fails to recover or dismisses his petition, the defendant may recover the property and its hire or the sworn value placed upon the property in the petition instead of suing on the replevy bond.</p>
          <p>(Code 1933, ยง 107-209.)</p>
